te via `python3 <file>` using `execute_command()`\n146:   - Raise `ValueError` for unsupported languages\n147:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n148:   - Verify: Python code executes correctly\n149: \n150: - [x] **T3.6** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.write_file()`\n151:   - Parameters: `content: str`, `remote_path: str`\n152:   - Base64 encode content\n153:   - POST JSON to `api/files`: `path`, `content`, `mode=\"0644\"`\n154:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n155:   - Verify: File created via base64 encoding\n156: \n157: - [x] **T3.7** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.upload_file()`\n158:   - Parameters: `local_path: str`, `remote_path: str`\n159:   - Read local file as binary\n160:   - POST multipart to `api/files` with `file`, `path`, `mode`\n161:   - Set `x-agentcube-session-id` header explicitly\n162:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n163:   - Verify: Multipart upload succeeds\n164: \n165: - [x] **T3.8** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.download_file()`\n166:   - Parameters: `remote_path: str`, `local_path: str`\n167:   - Clean path: `remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n168:   - GET from `api/files/{clean_path}` with `stream=True`\n169:   - Write chunks to local file\n170:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n171:   - Verify: File downloaded correctly\n172: \n173: - [x] **T3.9** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.list_files()`\n174:   - Parameter: `path: str = \".\"`\n175:   - GET from `api/files` with query `path`\n176:   - Return JSON response\n177:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n178:   - Verify: Returns file list\n179: \n180: - [x] **T3.10** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.close()`\n181:   - Call `self.session.close()`\n182:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n183:   - Verify: HTTP session closed\n184: \n185: - [x] **T3.11** Create `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n186:   - Import `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`, dependencies\n187:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n188:   - Verify: Module structure correct\n189: \n190: - [x] **T3.12** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.__init__()`\n191:   - Parameters: `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n192:   - Compute `base_url` from `router_url` + namespace + agent_name path using `urljoin()`\n193:   - Create session with `create_session()`\n194:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n195:   - Verify: Base URL computed correctly, connection pool configured (10/10)\n196: \n197: - [x] **T3.13** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id()`\n198:   - GET from `self.base_url`\n199:   - Read `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n200:   - Raise `ValueError` if header missing\n201:   - Return session ID\n202:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n203:   - Verify: Extracts session ID from response header\n204: \n205: - [x] **T3.14** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke()`\n206:   - Parameters: `session_id`, `payload: Dict[str, Any]`, `timeout: Optional[float]`\n207:   - Set headers: `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json`\n208:   - Apply timeout: `(connect_timeout, timeout)` or instance default\n209:   - POST JSON payload to `self.base_url`\n210:   - Return `requests.Response`\n211:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n212:   - Verify: Request sent with correct headers and timeout\n213: \n214: - [x] **T3.15** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.close()`\n215:   - Call `self.session.close()`\n216:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n217:   - Verify: HTTP session closed\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: ## Phase 4: Configuration & Environment Handling ✓\n222: \n223: - [x] **T4.1** Implement environment variable resolution for `ROUTER_URL`\n224:   - Check explicit parameter first\n225:   - Fall back to `os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\")`\n226:   - Raise `ValueError` if both missing\n227:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`, `code_interpreter.py`\n228:   - Verify: Env var fallback works, clear error on missing\n229: \n230: - [x] **T4.2** Implement environment variable resolution for `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`\n231:   - Check explicit parameter first\n232:   - Fall back to `os.getenv(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\")`\n233:   - Raise `ValueError` if both missing\n234:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n235:   - Verify: Env var fallback works, clear error on missing\n236: \n237: - [x] **T4.3** Implement timeout defaults\n238:   - Default `timeout=120` (read timeout)\n239:   - Default `connect_timeout=5.0`\n240:   - Use tuple form `(connect_timeout, read_timeout)` for requests\n241:   - File: All client `__init__` methods\n242:   - Verify: Timeouts applied correctly to HTTP requests\n243: \n244: - [x] **T4.4** Implement per-call timeout override\n245:   - Allow `timeout` parameter on `invoke()`, `execute_command()` methods\n246:   - Override instance default for that call only\n247:   - File: Data plane client methods\n248:   - Verify: Timeout override works per call\n249: \n250: - [x] **T4.5** Implement connection pool configuration\n251:   - Default `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n252:   - Pass to `create_session()` for all clients\n253:   - File: All client `__init__` methods\n254:   - Verify: Connection pools configured with 10/10\n255: \n256: ---\n257: \n258: ## Phase 5: Error Handling ✓\n259: \n260: - [x] **T5.1** Implement `ValueError` for missing URLs\n261:   - Check in `__init__` after resolving from env\n262:   - Message: `\"router_url must be provided or ROUTER_URL environment variable must be set\"`\n263:   - File: `agent_runtime.py`, `code_interpreter.py`, `control_plane.py`\n264:   - Verify: Clear error message on missing URL\n265: \n266: - [x] **T5.2** Implement `ValueError` for missing session header\n267:   - Check response header after bootstrap GET\n268:   - Message: `\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n269:   - File: `agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n270:   - Verify: Raised when header missing\n271: \n272: - [x] **T5.3** Implement `ValueError` for uninitialized session\n273:   - Check `session_id` before `invoke()`\n274:   - Message: `\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\"`\n275:   - File: `agent_runtime.py`\n276:   - Verify: Raised when invoke called without session\n277: \n278: - [x] **T5.4** Implement `CommandExecutionError` for non-zero exit\n279:   - Check `exit_code` after command execution\n280:   - Include `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command` in exception\n281:   - File: `code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n282:   - Verify: Raised with correct attributes on non-zero exit\n283: \n284: - [x] **T5.5** Handle 404 as idempotent success\n285:   - Return `True` on 404 in `delete_session()`\n286:   - Log warning for other error codes\n287:   - File: `control_plane.py`\n288:   - Verify: Delete is idempotent\n289: \n290: - [x] **T5.6** Propagate HTTP errors\n291:   - Call `response.raise_for_status()` after requests\n292:   - Allow `requests.HTTPError` and `requests.RequestException` to propagate\n293:   - File: All data plane methods\n294:   - Verify: HTTP errors raised to caller\n295: \n296: ---\n297: \n298: ## Phase 6: High-Level Client Integration ✓\n299: \n300: - [x] **T6.1** Create `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n301:   - Import `CodeInterpreterClient`, dependencies\n302:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n303:   - Verify: Module structure correct\n304: \n305: - [x] **T6.2** Implement `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__()`\n306:   - Parameters: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `auth_token`, `verbose`, `session_id`\n307:   - Create `ControlPlaneClient`\n308:   - Create session via `cp_client.create_session()` if `session_id` not provided\n309:   - Call `_init_data_plane()` with cleanup on failure\n310:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n311:   - Verify: Client instantiates, session created or reused\n312: \n313: - [x] **T6.3** Implement `CodeInterpreterClient._init_data_plane()`\n314:   - Create `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with session_id, router_url, namespace, name\n315:   - Store as `self.dp_client`\n316:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n317:   - Verify: Data plane client initialized\n318: \n319: - [x] **T6.4** Implement `CodeInterpreterClient.__enter__()` and `__exit__()`\n320:   - `__enter__`: return `self`\n321:   - `__exit__`: call `self.stop()`\n322:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n323:   - Verify: Context manager protocol works\n324: \n325: - [x] **T6.5** Implement `CodeInterpreterClient.stop()`\n326:   - Close data plane client\n327:   - Delete session via `cp_client.delete_session()`\n328:   - Close control plane client\n329:   - Log cleanup actions\n330:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n331:   - Verify: All resources cleaned up\n332: \n333: - [x] **T6.6** Implement delegation methods\n334:   - `execute_command(command, timeout)` → `dp_client.execute_command()`\n335:   - `run_code(language, code, timeout)` → `dp_client.run_code()`\n336:   - `write_file(content, remote_path)` → `dp_client.write_file()`\n337:   - `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` → `dp_client.upload_file()`\n338:   - `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` → `dp_client.download_file()`\n339:   - `list_files(path)` → `dp_client.list_files()`\n340:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n341:   - Verify: All methods delegate correctly\n342: \n343: - [x] **T6.7** Create `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n344:   - Import `AgentRuntimeClient`, dependencies\n345:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n346:   - Verify: Module structure correct\n347: \n348: - [x] **T6.8** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__()`\n349:   - Parameters: `agent_name`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `router_url`, `verbose`, `session_id`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`\n350:   - Store instance attributes\n351:   - Initialize logger with verbose level\n352:   - Resolve `router_url` from arg or `ROUTER_URL` env\n353:   - Create `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n354:   - Bootstrap session ID if not provided\n355:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n356:   - Verify: Client instantiates, session bootstrapped\n357: \n358: - [x] **T6.9** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.__enter__()` and `__exit__()`\n359:   - `__enter__`: return `self`\n360:   - `__exit__`: call `self.close()`\n361:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n362:   - Verify: Context manager protocol works\n363: \n364: - [x] **T6.10** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke()`\n365:   - Parameter: `payload: Dict[str, Any]`, `timeout: Optional[float]`\n366:   - Check `session_id` is set, raise `ValueError` if not\n367:   - Call `dp_client.invoke()` with session_id, payload, timeout\n368:   - Return `response.json()`\n369:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n370:   - Verify: Invocation returns JSON response\n371: \n372: - [x] **T6.11** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.close()`\n373:   - Close data plane client\n374:   - Log cleanup\n375:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n376:   - Verify: Resources cleaned up\n377: \n378: ---\n379: \n380: ## Phase 7: Session ID Management ✓\n381: \n382: - [x] **T7.1** Implement session header constant\n383:   - Define `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"` (lowercase)\n384:   - Use constant consistently across clients\n385:   - File: `agent_runtime_data_plane.py`, `code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n386:   - Verify: Header name consistent\n387: \n388: - [x] **T7.2** Implement session ID bootstrapping\n389:   - GET invocation endpoint to obtain session ID from response header\n390:   - Store session ID in client instance\n391:   - File: `agent_runtime.py`, `agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n392:   - Verify: Session ID obtained from Router\n393: \n394: - [x] **T7.3** Implement session ID header setting\n395:   - Set `x-agentcube-session-id` in session headers after bootstrap\n396:   - Include header in all data plane requests\n397:   - File: `agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n398:   - Verify: Header sent with all requests\n399: \n400: - [x] **T7.4** Implement explicit session ID support\n401:   - Allow `session_id` parameter in high-level clients\n402:   - Skip bootstrap when session_id provided\n403:   - File: `agent_runtime.py`, `code_interpreter.py`\n404:   - Verify: Reuses existing session when provided\n405: \n406: ---\n407: \n408: ## Phase 8: URL Path Building ✓\n409: \n410: - [x] **T8.1** Implement Router URL path building\n411:   - Use `urljoin()` for relative path拼接\n412:   - Path format: `/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n413:   - File: `agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n414:   - Verify: URL computed correctly\n415: \n416: - [x] **T8.2** Implement Workload Manager URL path building\n417:   - Path format: `/v1/code-interpreter` for create\n418:   - Path format: `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` for delete\n419:   - File: `control_plane.py`\n420:   - Verify: URLs computed correctly\n421: \n422: - [x] **T8.3** Implement Code Interpreter data plane URL building\n423:   - Support `api/execute`, `api/files`, `api/files/{path}`\n424:   - Use `urljoin()` for relative paths\n425:   - File: `code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n426:   - Verify: URLs computed correctly\n427: \n428: ---\n429: \n430: ## Acceptance Criteria\n431: \n432: 1. ✅ All HTTP endpoints follow spec-defined paths and parameters\n433: 2. ✅ Connection pool correctly configured (10/10)\n434: 3. ✅ Timeout behavior as expected (default 120s read / 5.0s connect)\n435: 4. ✅ Exception hierarchy complete (`AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, placeholders)\n436: 5. ✅ Environment variable resolution works (`ROUTER_URL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`)\n437: 6. ✅ Unit tests cover all scenarios (HTTP timeout, pool reuse, error cases)\n438: 7. ✅ Session header uses lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id`\n439: 8. ✅ Read timeout buffer (+2.0s) applied to command execution\n440: 9. ✅ Control plane handles 404 as idempotent success on delete\n441: 10. ✅ Data plane init failure triggers cleanup and re-raise\n442: 11. ✅ Router URL validation: `ValueError` if both arg and env missing\n443: 12. ✅ Bootstrap session ID from Router invocation endpoint\n444: 13. ✅ Per-call timeout override supported\n445: 14. ✅ `urljoin()` used for relative path building\n446: 15. ✅ All clients implement context manager protocol\n447: 16. ✅ Logging configured with verbose option\n448: 17. ✅ Package exports: `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient`\n449: 18. ✅ Clients export: `from agentcube.clients import ControlPlaneClient, ...`\n450: \n451: ---\n452: \n453: **Notes:**\n454: - Stage ST-3 marked complete: all HTTP clients and infrastructure implemented\n455: - Session header naming: uses lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` throughout\n456: - Timeout handling: read timeout gets +2.0s buffer for command execution to avoid premature `ReadTimeout`\n457: - Exception usage: `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` defined but not raised by core clients (reserved for future expansion)\n458: - Distributed configuration: no single `Configuration` class; each client resolves own settings from args/env\n459: - Connection pooling: all clients use `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` by default\n\n(End of file - total 459 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端 Tasks\n\n**Module:** sdk-python  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Package Structure & Utilities ✓\n\n- [x] **T1.1** Create `agentcube/__init__.py`\n  - Import `CodeInterpreterClient` from `code_interpreter`\n  - Import `AgentRuntimeClient` from `agent_runtime`\n  - Define `__all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py`\n  - Verify: `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient` works\n\n- [x] **T1.2** Create `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n  - Define `AgentCubeError(Exception)` base class","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-029/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775878379351,"end":1775878379367}}}}
